      "orig": "The columns of this matrix are multiples of the column of A and the rows are multiples of the row of B .  If we think of the entries in these rows as the coordinates ( 2, 12 ) or ( 3, 18 ) or ( 4, 24 ) ,  all  these  points  lie  on  the  same  line; similarly for the two column vectors.  Later we'll see that this is equivalent to saying that the row space of this matrix is a single line, as is the column space .",
