      "orig": "As in the last lecture, we can write the results of the elimination method as the product of a number of elimination matrices Eij with the matrix A . Letting E be the product of all the Eij , we write the result of this Gauss-Jordan elimination using block matrices: E [ A | I ] = [ I | E ] . But if EA = I , then E = A -1 .",
      "text": "As in the last lecture, we can write the results of the elimination method as the product of a number of elimination matrices Eij with the matrix A . Letting E be the product of all the Eij , we write the result of this Gauss-Jordan elimination using block matrices: E [ A | I ] = [ I | E ] . But if EA = I , then E = A -1 ."
